sql:
SELECT AVG(grad_rate) AS average_grad_rate
FROM graduation_rates
WHERE grad_rate > 55;

SELECT acceptance_rate
FROM application_stats
WHERE institution_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- 'Gems' refers to institutions that are highly regarded and have strict admission criteria; 
- 'high demand for excellence' refers to institutions with acceptance rates of 75% or less and the top 10% of high school performers being 50% or more of the student body; 
- 'treasure trove of resources' refers to institutions with an endowment of $500,000,000 or more.

sql:
SELECT AVG(acceptance_rate) AS average_acceptance_rate
FROM application_stats
WHERE total_apps > 2000 AND yield_rate > 50.0;

SELECT average_salary
FROM alumni_outcomes
WHERE institution_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
High graduation rates refer to graduation rates of 70% or higher; 
Private institutions are those that are not publicly funded; 
Total student enrollment numbers include both full-time and part-time undergraduates.

- 'Venerable institutions' refers to institutions that were founded before 1950; 
- 'High flying colors' refers to the institutions' graduation rates being 70% or higher; 
- 'Substantial financial success' means having average salaries greater than $50,000.
